.TH "CIRCLECI-MIGRATE" "1" "Jun 2026" "circleci-migrate" "CircleCI Org Migration CLI"

.SH NAME
circleci-migrate-orb-inline - Inline private-orb references into a CircleCI config file.


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBcircleci-migrate orb inline [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
inline fetches the published YAML source of each orb referenced in the
supplied config file and replaces the external reference with an inline orb
definition, removing the dependency on the orb namespace.

.PP
This is intended as a temporary workaround during the migration overlap window
when the source org's private orbs are not yet resolvable in the destination
org.  REVERT the change once the namespace has been transferred.

.PP
WARNING: YAML comments and anchors are NOT preserved by the round-trip
serialisation.  For comment-preserving rewrites, apply the change manually.

.PP
Example:
  circleci-migrate orb inline \\
    --config .circleci/config.yml \\
    --namespace myns \\
    --output .circleci/config.inlined.yml


.SH OPTIONS
\fB--config\fP=""
	Path to the .circleci/config.yml file to rewrite (required)

.PP
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for inline

.PP
\fB--namespace\fP=""
	Only inline orbs whose namespace matches this value (empty = inline all)

.PP
\fB-o\fP, \fB--output\fP=""
	Output path (default: stdout)


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--debug\fP[=false]
	Enable debug logging

.PP
\fB--dest-token\fP=""
	API token for the destination org (env: CIRCLECI_DEST_TOKEN)

.PP
\fB--host\fP="https://circleci.com"
	CircleCI host URL (env: CIRCLECI_HOST)

.PP
\fB--source-token\fP=""
	API token for the source org (env: CIRCLECI_SOURCE_TOKEN)

.PP
\fB--token\fP=""
	Personal API token — fallback for both orgs (env: CIRCLECI_CLI_TOKEN)


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBcircleci-migrate-orb(1)\fP
